cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.HC, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the application of blockchain technology to clinical data sharing, which involves security and privacy concerns (cs.CR). It also involves the management and storage of large amounts of data (cs.DB), as well as the design and implementation of a decentralized system (cs.DC). The paper also focuses on the use of the HL7 FHIR standard for clinical data exchange (cs.HC), and the development of a decentralized app (cs.SE).
